Name Rascal/Expressions/Values/Number/GreaterThanOrEqual

Synopsis Greater than or equal operator on numeric values.
Syntax Exp1 >= Exp2
Types
Exp1 Exp2 Exp1 >= Exp2
int int bool
int real bool
real real bool
Description Yields true if the value of Exp1 is numerically greather than or equal to the value of Exp2, and false otherwise.
Examples 
rascal>13 >= 12
bool: true
rascal>12 >= 13
bool: false
rascal>13.5 >= 12
bool: true
rascal>12.5 >= 13
bool: false
